Description:
LUCY IN DISGUISE WITH DIAMONDS
"Can't buy me love, but you can buy me 24 Lucy Crescent."
And ain't she sweet. With contemporary flair and style, 24 Lucy Crescent is sure to be a hit, let it be your next purchase. Only a few minutes walk from Officer Secondary School and even closer to public transport, your searchin' is finally over the moment you step through the door. Surrounded by the ever-expanding Officer community and not even two years old, 24 Lucy Crescent is your ticket to ride.
On a large 512m2 block (approx.), the house features:
- Two enormous living zones;
- Separate dining area;
- Widespread kitchen centrally located;
- Four bedrooms, large master with walk-in robe and en-suite;
- Alfresco overlooking the manicured gardens.
No more crying, waiting, hoping. Spend a day in the life of 24 Lucy Crescent and you'll be here 8 days a week.
First inspection is this Saturday, you'd be a madman to miss it.

BY GEORGE, I THINK WE'VE GOT IT!
"Located on the fairer side of town comes the area's most affordable four-bedroom property."
Have you been looking to crack in to the Officer market but can't afford any of the four bedroom properties on the market? Then you need to inspect 30 Georgetown Way.
The genuine four bedroom property is walking distance from Arena shopping centre, Cardinia Railway station and located within the Officer Secondary School zoning.
Featuring:
- Master with walk-in robe and en-suite and remaining bedrooms with double robes;
- Open plan living, dining area;
- Great-sized kitchen with large marble bench tops;
- High ceilings adorned with gas ducted heating and evaporative cooling;
- Alfresco;
- Double garage with internal access.
See you at the inspection :)
